The Marlin Camp Carbine is a auto-loading carbine chambered for either 9mm Parabellum (or .45 ACP), formerly manufactured by Marlin Firearms Company of North Haven, Connecticut. The carbine started production in 1985 and has been discontinued since 1999.

As the name implies, it was designed as a utility firearm to be used around hunting camps for foraging or defense. The 9mm Parabellum uses the same magazines as popular handguns in this calibers, in keeping with a convenient American tradition of having a carbine and handgun using common ammunition. The carbine operates by direct blowback. Usually, the receiver is drilled and tapped for a scope mount. The stock was made of walnut-finished Maine birch.

The Camp 9 Carbine uses a detachable magazine that inserts into the magazine well in front of the trigger guard. The Camp-9 rifle magazine can be replaced by magazines from 59-series S&W pistols. The Camp-9 magazine well is sized for 12-round magazines; magazines with higher capacities extend beyond the bottom of the well. A 20-round magazine was produced, but discontinued in 1989.
*** Must be legal to own this firearm and willing to show ID/sign a bill of sale."

Please email us with any suggestions for improvement.  Please do not leave negative feedback without contacting us via phone or email to discuss the problem at hand.  Most cases can be mediated.

Factory new items are sold as is.  The warranty is to be handled through the original manufacturer.  We will accept returns with prior notice only.  Notice is to be made within a 3 day inspection period from which the merchandise was received. We will issue a 100% refund if we made a mistake in our listing. There will be a 25% restocking fee on all returned items.  Merchandise must still be sealed and as new.  All used merchandise must be in the same shape it left our store in.  Condition will be evaluated when it is received back.  There are no refunds on listings stated ""AS IS"" in the description. We will not refund any shipping cost or auction fees. All parts should be fitted by qualified personnel. Please email or call if you have any questions before purchasing.

Our contact information is available at our website. You can also ask a question via Ebay, Gunbroker, or the website in which you found our listing on. The winning bidder needs to have paid or made contact with us within 3 business days after the auction ending. We are open to trades and offers.

As these items are for sale in multiple venues, we reserve the right to cancel the sale at any time.  On rare occasion we may sell out of an item before we are able to remove it from out listing.  In such an instance we will do our best to either provide the buyer with an equivalent product, discount another product, cancel the sale, or issue a full refund if payment has already been made.  We do our best to avoid these situations, but we are all human and it happens.  Thank you for understanding.

776,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3949776,"For Sale/Trade:  Soviet Mosin Nagant PU Sniper M91/30 w/Bent Bolt, Beautiful Wood Stock","Martinsburg/Charlestown/Inwood/Hedgesville, Martinsburg, West Virginia",$ 315,"Listed On: Tuesday, March 24, 2015",Rifles,Mauser                                                                                ,7.62x54R                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Rifle,"Beautiful wood stock and historically accurate ex-Sniper PU Mosin Nagant M91/30 with filled scope holes and true sniper bent belt. She is a genuine ex-sniper Mosin Nagant PU Sniper dated to the end of WW2 era 1944 and will make a great addition to your collection ""as is"" or could very easily be converted back into an original PU Sniper Mosin with the addition of a SVT scope. This Mosin rifle has an Izhevsk marked Russian ""Hammer & Sickle"" high wall receiver (the only receiver type chosen as suitable for a true sniper). She has been refinished to very good condition and has a ""smoothed up"" crisp light trigger action and an absolutely beautiful wood grain stock. This PU Sniper Mosin HAS NOT been counter-bored and the bore shines with excellent clear and deep rifling. The original scope mount holes in the receiver have been arsenal filled but could be easily tapped out if one desired to convert her back into an original sniper PU rifle with SVT scope and base mount. The possibilities are limitless with this base genuine PU bent bolt ex-sniper Mosin Nagant rifle. I tried to take many close up pictures to accurately capture the fine craftsmanship found on this historic Russian PU Sniper. The wood stock is in excellent condition and you can clearly ""see"" the cutout and professional repair for where they had previously mounted a sniper scope to the receiver. This wood repair could easily be removed to facilitate another scope installation or makes for a fine conversation piece when sharing the history of this rifle with your friends. Again, many possibilities exist with this unique ex-sniper bent bolt combination. Feel free to ask any questions. I will ship to C&R holders or to your FFL if desired. As you may have noticed, the importation of all Mosin Nagants has dried up considerably and genuine Sniper PU Mosins are almost impossible to find anywhere anymore. As such this de-commissioned ex-Sniper Mosin will likely become a fine investment.
Email or call/text REDACTED,  I am open to trades of all kinds."

Without a doubt the Mosin Nagant M91/30 provides by far the most bang for the buck of any rifle on the market today. 926,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3949926,For Sale:  PWS MK1 Mod 1,"New Richmond, Ohio, Cincinnati, Ohio","$ 1,600","Listed On: Monday, May 4, 2015",Rifles,no type,223/5.56 NATO                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"A model developed after the M4 pattern rifle, the PWS MK114 Rifle has quickly become the crowd favorite for those wanting a compact package without the NFA paperwork associated with shorter barrels. The MK114 retains lethal capability out to 500 meters with varying types of ammunition and boasts a permanently attached FSC556.

Utilizing the proven system originally designed for the MK107, the MK114 uses a mid length gas piston system. The operating system, designed after the venerable AK-47, features a long stroke fixed operating rod design with an adjustable gas block, 15 handguard and free-floated barrel.
The handguard features the VLTOR KeyMod System which comes standard with two 2 sections of 1913 rail as well as a continuous 1913 top rail.

Understanding the importance of an ultra-reliable package that is light as possible, mil-spec forgings are used for the upper and lower receiver. Additional features include the BCM GUNFIGHTER charging handle, the PWS enhanced buffer tube and an ALG Defense QMS trigger. The rifle is rounded out with industry leading features such as Magpul MOE grip, MOE stock, and MBUS2 sights.
PWS Forged Mil-Spec Upper and Lower Receiver
If you have any questions please let me know, thanks for looking.
A 4473 is required for purchase. Cash or check only please. All sales will be charged sales tax. At this time I do not offer any layaway options. Thank you.

This is a real tack driver for a great price and is fun to shoot. If you like the metallic sound of silhouettes falling you’ll love this weapon.
It has a 24” crowned, bull barrel with 1:10 twist, free floating in a Michaels of Oregon stock. The trigger is match grade and breaks very nicely.

The optics are a Springfield Armory Gen 2 Government scope with built in range finder, .308 Bullet drop compensator and internal bubble level to eliminate any canting of the system on those long shots (selling for $750 on ebay). With this scope you don’t have to take your eye off the target to determine range and ensure there is no cant in your hold. When I took it out to the range the first day, I shot the groups you see below at 100 yards and I am not the best shot.
The weapon comes with a Harris bi-pod, Leupold scope mount and rings, Eagle shooting mat, Dewey cleaning rods and bore alignment tool to ensure you don’t scratch the barrel during cleaning.

The sale also comes with the original Savage stock in which the barrel is pillar mounted if you decide to go back to basics. I’ll also throw in the .50 cal ammo can to help organize your trip to the range.  I’ve put about 75 rounds through this system, which is just about enough to break it in.
Asking $950 for everything.  Please text Dan at 614-four two zero-0309. Face to face cash transactions only please."
